Class NumericArrayList<N extends Number>

java.lang.Object
java.util.AbstractCollection<E>

java.util.ArrayList<E>
civitas.celestis.util.collection.GroupableArrayList<N>
civitas.celestis.util.collection.NumericArrayList<N>
Type Parameters:
N - The type of number this list should hold
All Implemented Interfaces:
GroupableCollection<N>, GroupableList<N>, Filterable<N>, Groupable<N>, Transformable<N>, Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<N>, Collection<N>, List<N>, RandomAccess
public class NumericArrayList<N extends Number> extends GroupableArrayList<N>
A GroupableArrayList which contains a subtype of Number. The signs of the component numbers can be extracted by calling getSigns().

    • merge

      @Nonnull public NumericArrayList<N> merge(@Nonnull List<N> l, @Nonnull BiFunction<? super N,? super N,N> f) throws IllegalArgumentException
      Merges this list with another list of the same size. The merger function f is applied to each component, and the resulting list is returned.

      For example, if a sum function (x, y) -> x + y was provided, this would return the sum of the two lists of numbers.

      Overrides:

      Parameters:

      Returns:
      The resulting list
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - When the provided list l's size is different from that of this list's
